# Util – Auth and Upload

## auth.js

- JWT with `jsonwebtoken`: `generateToken(user)`, `verifyToken(token)`.
- Middleware `authenticate(req, res, next)` – read `Authorization: Bearer <token>`, set `req.user` from payload, call `next()`. On failure respond with 401 and `{ message }`.
- Do not put route-specific logic here; keep helpers reusable.

## upload.js

- Use multer for file uploads. In routes use e.g. `upload.single('image')`; file is available as `req.file` (e.g. `req.file.filename`).

Reference: `util/auth.js` for the middleware pattern.
